The paper deals with community detection in graphs, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of social network analysis and machine learning. The use of random processes and graph algorithms suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The focus on graph structures and their properties makes cs.SD (Systems and Control) another likely category. The use of mathematical tools such as concentration bounds and matrix analysis suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
